## MVP content ceiling

One zone (Red Mesa), three frames, three resource families, survey + deploy + claim thumper, a few recipes, durability, inventory ledger. Defer everything else.

## Cost-aware design

- Server-authoritative actions; ledger every economy mutation.
- Resolve thumper progress from timestamps, not per-second ticks.
- HTTP + light polling first; no WebSockets/SSE until proven necessary.
- Postgres-backed jobs before Redis or external queues.
